The paper presents an algorithm to generate synthetic datasets for classification of Morse code symbols for supervised machine learning problems, particularly neural networks. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also explores how network performance is affected by adding noise and expanding the feature set and dataset size, which could fall under neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
